def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Test Hypothesis 1 and 2 by generating images of animals and non-animals, and animal heads
    prompt_list = [
        "a dog sitting in a room", 
        "a car parked on the street",
        "a cat's face close up",
        "a laptop on a desk"
    ]
    images = tools.text2image(prompt_list)
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    
    # Document the experiment results and the tested hypotheses
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, prompt_list, "Experiment to test neuron selectivity for animals and animal heads.")
    
    # Test Hypothesis 3 by generating images with and without furry textures
    prompt_list_furry = [
        "a furry dog",
        "the same dog with short hair",
        "a hairy tarantula",
        "a smooth glass ball"
    ]
    images_furry = tools.text2image(prompt_list_furry)
    activation_list_furry, activation_map_list_furry = system.call_neuron(images_furry)
    
    # Document the experiment results and the tested hypotheses
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list_furry, activation_map_list_furry, prompt_list_furry, "Experiment to test neuron selectivity for furry textures.")
    
    # Test Hypothesis 4
    prompt_ears = [
        "an elephant with large ears",
        "the same elephant without ears",
        "a rabbit with large ears",
        "the same rabbit without ears"
    ]
    images_ears = tools.text2image(prompt_ears)
    activation_list_ears, activation_map_list_ears = system.call_neuron(images_ears)
    
    # Document the experiment results and the tested hypotheses
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list_ears, activation_map_list_ears, prompt_ears, "Experiment to test neuron selectivity for animal ears.")
```

def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Additional experiment testing the selectivity for furry animals
    prompt_list_furry_animals = [
        "a close-up image of a furry wolf",
        "a close-up image of a wolf with digitally removed fur",
        "a bear walking through the forest",
        "a sphinx cat sitting on a cushion"
    ]
    
    images_furry_animals = tools.text2image(prompt_list_furry_animals)
    activation_list_furry_animals, activation_map_list_furry_animals = system.call_neuron(images_furry_animals)
    
    # Document the experiment results
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list_furry_animals, activation_map_list_furry_animals, prompt_list_furry_animals, "Additional experiment on furry animals.")
    
    # Check against non-living things with similar texture as fur to disentangle fur texture from animal concept
    prompt_textures_similar_to_fur = [
        "a shaggy brown carpet",
        "a fluffy white towel",
        "cotton balls in a jar",
        "a smooth tile floor"
    ]
    
    images_textures = tools.text2image(prompt_textures_similar_to_fur)
    activation_list_textures, activation_map_list_textures = system.call_neuron(images_textures)
    
    # Document the experiment results
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list_textures, activation_map_list_textures, prompt_textures_similar_to_fur, "Textured objects experiment versus smooth surfaces.")
```

The activations for the textured objects that resemble fur, such as the shaggy carpet and fluffy towel, were relatively low compared to the high activations we observed for images of furry animals. This suggests that while texture may have some influence, it is likely not the primary factor. The very low activation for the smooth tile floor reinforces the idea that the neuron is sensitive to some form of texture, yet the consistently highest activations are with animals.

Therefore, we can consolidate our hypothesis to conclude that the neuron is highly selective for animals with fur, potentially combining both the representation of the animal itself and its furry texture as the visual concept that maximally activates it.

[DESCRIPTION]: This neuron is highly selective for images of furry animals. The activation is stronger for the visual concept including the characteristic furry texture of animals.
